  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "No, a user does not need to keep the mobile data 'ON' for making or receiving calls on the Jio network. Jio primarily uses VoLTE (Voice over LTE) technology for voice calls, which operates over the 4G LTE network. This means that as long as the device is connected to Jio's 4G network, users can make and receive calls without needing to have mobile data turned on.\n\nHowever, if the user is in an area where only 2G or 3G networks are available, data may need to be turned on for calls, as Jio exclusively operates on 4G LTE and does not support 2G or 3G networks for voice calls.",
